quran[62]{c,v,t}:
  37,83,Abraham was of the same faith
  37,84,he came to his Lord with a sound heart
  37,85,"Behold!\" he said to his father and to his people, \"What are these that you worship"
  37,86,Would you serve false deities instead of God
  37,87,What do you think of the Lord of the Worlds
  37,88,He looked up at the stars
  37,89,"And said, \"I am sick"
  37,90,so they turned their backs on him and went off
  37,91,"He turned to their gods and said, \"Do you not eat"
  37,92,What is the matter with you that you do not speak
  37,93,"then he turned on them, striking them down with his right hand"
  37,94,His people came rushing towards him
  37,95,"but he said, \"How can you worship things you carve with your own hands"
  37,96,when it is God who has created you and all your handiwork
  37,97,"They said, \"Build a pyre for him and throw him into the blaze"
  37,98,"They wanted to harm him, but We humiliated them all"
  37,99,"He said, \"I will go to my Lord: He is sure to guide me"
  37,100,"Lord, grant me a righteous son"
  37,101,"We gave him the good news that he would have a patient, forbearing son"
  37,102,"And when he reached the age when he could work with him, he said, \"O my son, I have seen in a dream that I am sacrificing you. So tell me what you think of it!\" He replied, \"O my father, do as you are commanded; and God willing, you will find me steadfast"
  37,103,"When they had both submitted to God, and he had laid his son down on his face"
  37,104,"We called out to him, \"Abraham"
  37,105,"you have fulfilled the dream.\" It is thus indeed that We reward those who do good"
  37,106,that surely was a manifest trial
  37,107,We ransomed him with a great sacrifice
  37,108,"and left him thus to be succeeded by a group [of followers] among later generations"
  37,109,Peace and salutation to Abraham
  37,110,That is how We recompense the righteous
  37,111,"truly, he was one of Our faithful servants"
  37,112,"We gave Abraham the good news of Isaac, a prophet and a righteous man"
  37,113,"and blessed him and Isaac too: some of their offspring were good, but some clearly sinned against their souls"
  37,114,We also bestowed Our favour on Moses and Aaron
  37,115,We saved them and their people from great distress
  37,116,"and We helped them, so that they were victorious"
  37,117,and We gave them the Book which helps to make things clear
  37,118,and guided them to the straight path
  37,119,"and We left them thus to be succeeded by a group [of followers] among later generations"
  37,120,Peace be upon Moses and Aaron
  37,121,This is how We reward those who do good
  37,122,truly they were among Our faithful servants
  37,123,Elijah too was one of the messengers
  37,124,"He said to his people, \"Have you no fear [of God]"
  37,125,Do you call on Baal and abandon the Best of Creators
  37,126,God your Lord and Lord of your forefathers
  37,127,"but they rejected him, and thus will certainly be called to account"
  37,128,except the chosen servants of God
  37,129,"We left him thus to be succeeded by a group [of followers] among the following generations"
  37,130,Peace be on Elijah and his people
  37,131,It is thus indeed that We reward those who do good
  37,132,surely he was one of Our believing servants
  37,133,Lot was also one of the messengers
  37,134,We saved him and all his people
  37,135,except for an old woman who stayed behind
  37,136,and We destroyed the rest
  37,137,You pass by their ruins morning
  37,138,"and night: will you not take heed"
  37,139,Jonah too was one of the messengers
  37,140,He fled to the overloaded ship
  37,141,And then they cast lots and he was the one who lost
  37,142,and the fish swallowed him while he was blaming himself
  37,143,Had he not been one of those who acknowledge the glory of God
  37,144,he would certainly have remained inside the fish till the Day of Resurrection